The Total Error was Obtained Considering
Systematic and Random Errors, Including Uncertainties
In Target and Monitor Thickness, Decay Curve Analysis,
Chemical Yield, Monitor Cross Section and Decay Scheme
Data. The Uncertainty of the Proton Beam is +-20  MeV.
All Targets were Sandwiched Between Three 1 Mil Al
Foils on Each Side. The Outer Foils Compensated For
The Recoiling Na-24 Nuclei from the Monitor Foil,
The Monitor Foils Served to Measure the Beam Intensity,
And the Inner Foils Compensated For the Recoiling Na-24
Nuclei from the Monitor Foil and Served As Catcher
Foil For any Product Nuclei Recoiling from the Target.
Thus the Inner Catcher Foils were Dissolved Together
With the Target Before Chemical Separation.
